data.description: Once in a lifetime find in Knottingham Estates of Old Woodway with almost 2,200 square feet of dwelling space on one-third of an acre! The home opens to wrap-around, floor-to-ceiling bookshelves in the library as well as coffered ceilings. Living space features a large salvaged brick hearth, exposed wood beams, wood tile flooring, and vaulted ceiling. Directly off of the library and living room lies the galley kitchen and eating area. Upgraded cabinetry, extra storage space, giant picture window, and double oven create the perfect spot to host any get-together. One minor bedroom and the utility room sit off of the kitchen. The primary suite shines with custom molding giving a timeless craftsman feel to the space. The en suite boasts of a custom wood vanity, hammered copper sink, walk-in shower, and large closet. Minor bedrooms are spacious, and come with built-ins. Be sure to check out the trimwork galore! Tons of cabinets and storage space, too. Outside, mature oak and ash trees are scattered along this corner lot, providing the perfect amount of shade for outdoor living. A covered patio, established flower beds, river rock trucked in from Colorado, boat storage, and enormous workshop with electricity offer endless opportunities to enjoy the property. Windows replaced in November of 2018, and come with a 30-year transferable warranty. HVAC replaced, air scrubber installed, and plenum rebuilt in September 2021. Partial fence line rebuilt in 2022 with custom iron gates from Ascend Ironworks. Call your REALTOR today! This charmer is a must-see!
